commit_message:
Add test for disabling, enabling project (Identity->Projects)

1) Create new project in enabled state;
2) Disable it and check that its state in 'Enabled' column is 'No';
3) Enable it and check that its state in 'Enabled' column is 'Yes';
4) Delete created project.

Implements blueprint: horizon-integration-tests-coverage
Change-Id: Iccf3edca908433a68b3c500958c17954dac96a09

Add test to check new project creation during new user creation.

Actions:
1) Go to Identity -> Users;
2) Create new user in 'admin' project with 'admin' role;
3) In create user form press create new project;
4) Fill project name and submit changes;
5) Check that creation will be successful and new user presents on User page;
6) Go to Project pages and check that new project presents on page;
7) In 'Manage Members' for project check that new user is in active project members;
8) Delete created project and user.

Implements blueprint: horizon-integration-tests-coverage
Change-Id: I8d159eda911fe2a92563097a3ec3137cc0d2a787
